PHASE 2 — AUTH SYSTEM: SIGN-UP, SIGN-IN, SIGN-OUT
══════════════════════════════════════════════

Fix and implement all of the following so they work perfectly:

1. POST /api/auth/register
   - Validate with Zod: email, password (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase,
     1 number), firstName, lastName
   - Check for duplicate email in DB (Drizzle query)
   - Hash password with bcryptjs (12 rounds)
   - Create user record + user data record (demo balance: $10,000)
   - Create session record, set httpOnly + secure + sameSite=strict
     cookie with session token
   - Return: { user: { id, email, firstName, lastName, role } }
   - Fire-and-forget welcome email if SMTP is configured

2. POST /api/auth/login
   - Validate with Zod: email, password
   - Query DB with Drizzle. Compare password with bcryptjs.
   - Account lockout: 5 failed attempts locks for 15 minutes
   - On success: create new session, set cookie, log IP + user agent
   - Return: { user: { id, email, firstName, lastName, role } }

3. POST /api/auth/logout
   - Delete session from DB, clear session cookie
   - Return 200: { message: "Logged out successfully" }

4. POST /api/auth/demo/login
   - Create or reuse a demo user account (role: DEMO)
   - Demo account always starts with $10,000 demo balance
   - Set demo session cookie (24h expiry)
   - Return: { user: { id, email, role: "DEMO" }, isDemo: true }

5. POST /api/auth/demo/logout
   - Clear demo session and cookie
   - Return 200

6. GET /api/auth/me
   - Read session token from cookie
   - Look up session in DB, verify not expired
   - Return current user profile + user data

7. Middleware: requireAuth(req, res, next)
   - Read session token from cookie
   - Look up session in DB (Drizzle), check expiry
   - Attach req.userId, req.user, req.role to request
   - Return 401 with clear JSON message if invalid/expired

8. Middleware: requireAdmin(req, res, next)
   - Calls requireAuth first
   - Checks req.role === 'ADMIN'
   - Return 403 JSON if not admin

9. Middleware: requireNotDemo(req, res, next)
   - Checks req.role !== 'DEMO'
   - Return 403: { error: "Demo accounts cannot perform this
     action. Please register for a real account." }

